article.headline: Siena 97, Marist 88
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. (AP) -- Kenny Hasbrouck scored 35 points, leading Siena to a 97-88 win in overtime over Marist in Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference basketball Friday. Hasbrouck shot 14-of-21 from the floor and made 5-of-7 3-pointers. Edwin Ubiles added 21 points for Siena, Ronald Moore scored 12, and Alex Franklin contributed 10 points. Siena (15-8, 10-3) shot 50 percent from the field and was 8-of-16 on 3-pointers. Jay Gavin led Marist (14-10, 8-5) with 19 points and 6 rebounds. Spongy Benjamin added 17 and had 8 rebounds. Ryan Stilphen scored 16 points and had 8 rebounds. Marist shot 54 percent from the field and made 8-of-16 3-point tries. Hasbrouck tied the game with a layup with 15 seconds left, and Jay Gavin turned the ball over on the Red Foxes, leading to the overtime. A Franklin's layup on Siena's first overtime possession gave the Saints the lead for good. Hasbrouck's two 3-pointers pushed the lead to 89-83 with 1:50 left and the Saints made their free throws down the stretch.
